# ⚙️ Batch Configuration

```java
@Bean
public Job retryFailedTransfersJob(JobRepository jobRepository,
                                   Step retryFailedTransfersStep) {

    return new JobBuilder("retryFailedTransfersJob", jobRepository)
            .start(retryFailedTransfersStep)
            .build();
}

@Bean
public Step retryFailedTransfersStep(JobRepository jobRepository,
                                     PlatformTransactionManager transactionManager,
                                     RetryFailedTransfersTasklet tasklet) {

    return new StepBuilder("retryFailedTransfersStep", jobRepository)
            .tasklet(tasklet, transactionManager)
            .build();
}
```

---

# 🕒 Scheduling

Run every **15–30 minutes**:

```
retryFailedTransfersJob
```

Spring example:

```java
@Scheduled(cron = "0 */30 * * * *")
public void retryFailedTransfers() {
    jobLauncher.run(retryFailedTransfersJob,
        new JobParametersBuilder()
            .addLong("timestamp", System.currentTimeMillis())
            .toJobParameters());
}
```

---

# 🛡 Safety Protections (Recommended)

### Limit retries per run

Example:

```
maxRetriesPerRun = 50
```

Prevents retry batch from running forever if thousands accumulate.

---

### Skip very old files

Optional:

```
failed/
   file.zip.pgp
   file.retry3.zip.pgp
```

You could stop retrying after **N attempts** later.

Not necessary initially.

